------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------- ResponseEntity -------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------

ResponseEntity = powerful way to return body + status code + headers in Spring Boot APIs.
Helps avoid always returning 200 OK, which can confuse clients.
Makes APIs RESTful, reliable, and more informative.

âš™ï¸ Why Use ResponseEntity?
    --> Allows custom response per situation (success, not found, error).
    --> Lets you add headers (e.g., pagination, authentication).
    --> Works seamlessly with generic response types (String, Object, DTOs, JSON).
    --> Improves frontend experience (React, Angular, Flutter, etc. can handle status easily).
    --> Encourages cleaner controller code (logic decides status).


====> ğŸŒ HTTP Status Codes ğŸŒ <====

âœ… 2xx â†’ Success
    --> 200 OK â†’ Standard success. The request worked, and data is returned.
    --> 201 Created â†’ A new resource has been successfully created (e.g., new user added).
    --> 204 No Content â†’ Request successful but no body/data is returned (common for `DELETE`).

âš ï¸ 3xx â†’ Redirection
    --> 301 Moved Permanently â†’ Resource URL has permanently changed.
    --> 302 Found â†’ Temporary redirection. Client should look at another URL. and also provides temp url for redirection

âŒ 4xx â†’ Client Errors
    --> 400 Bad Request â†’ The client sent invalid data (wrong JSON format, missing field, etc.).
    --> 401 Unauthorized â†’ Authentication required or token missing/invalid.
    --> 403 Forbidden â†’ You are authenticated but **not allowed** to access the resource.
    --> 404 Not Found â†’ The resource does not exist (wrong ID, invalid URL).

ğŸ’¥ 5xx â†’ Server Errors
    --> 500 Internal Server Error â†’ Unexpected error on the server side (null pointer, DB crash, etc.).
    --> 503 Service Unavailable â†’ Server is temporarily down or overloaded.








